article.headline: Bradley 74, Indiana St. 58
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Jeremy Crouch scored 13 points to lead the Bradley starters in double figures Saturday on the way to a 74-58 win over Indiana State. The Braves (20-11, 10-8 Missouri Valley) led 34-30 at halftime, but shot 49 percent form the floor over the final 20 minutes to pull away. Bradley led by as many as 19 points with four minutes left in the game. Indiana State shot 38 percent during the second half, and made 8-of-14 from the foul line. Daniel Ruffin and JJ. Tauai scored 12 points apiece for Bradley, with Ruffin also snagging seven rebounds. Will Franklin added 11 points, and Each Andrews chipped in 10 for the Braves. Both teams were aggressive from long range. Indiana State went 8-of-18 on it's three-point attempts, while the Braves made 10-of-29. Jay Tunnel scored 14 points to lead the Sycamores (12-17, 5-13 Missouri Valley), and Adam Arnold grabbed a game-high 11 rebounds.
